sentences: Choi Ye-won (Korean: 최예원; born June 18, 1999), known professionally as Arin, is a South Korean singer and actress.

section: == Career == | === 2015–2019: Debut with Oh My Girl and other activities ===

sentences: On April 20, 2015, Arin debuted as a member of Oh My Girl.
section: == Career == | === 2015–2019: Debut with Oh My Girl and other activities ===

sentences: She first performed their debut single on SBS MTV's The Show on April 21.
section: == Career == | === 2015–2019: Debut with Oh My Girl and other activities ===

sentences: On April 2, 2018, Arin debuted in Oh My Girl's first sub-unit, Oh My Girl Banhana.
section: == Career == | === 2015–2019: Debut with Oh My Girl and other activities ===

sentences: On September 7, 2019, it was announced that Arin would be appearing on XtvN's The Ultimate Watchlist 2.
section: == Career == | === 2015–2019: Debut with Oh My Girl and other activities ===

sentences: In August 2019, it was confirmed that Arin would be taking part in Queendom.
section: == Career == | === 2015–2019: Debut with Oh My Girl and other activities ===

sentences: On March 10, 2020, Arin was cast as Oh Na-ri in Naver TV's web series The World of My 17.
On July 20, 2020, Arin was announced as the new host for Music Bank with Choi Soo-bin of TXT.
Their last broadcast from the role was on October 1, 2021.
In March 2021, it was announced that Arin was cast in Netflix's series Ghost Story 2.
On June 18, 2021, it was announced that Arin donated ₩30 million to The Beautiful Foundation in honor of her 22nd birthday.
On March 5, 2020, Arin became the brand model for South Korean clothing brand BYC.
